                  <p>Martyr</p>
               </state>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl1171-1">AMS, II, 397-441 ; BHO, 177. Hoffmann, Auszuge, 17- 19. Suhadii', I, 291- 306. DHGE, VI, col. 477 (A. van Lantschoot) , avec references, et toute Ia litterature sur le couvent rassemblee dans Assyrie chretienne, II, 565- 613. H. Younansardaroud, "Die Legende von Mar Behnam", in M. Tamcke, ed. , Syriaca (Wittenberg, 2002), 185- 96.</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="dates" source="#bibl1171-1"> </note>
               <note type="abstract">Behnām and his sister Sarah were high-born Christian martyrs who were the children of Sennacherib. They converted to Christianity through a monk, Mattai, and were killed by their father. Their father later repented and became a Christian and with his wife Queen Shirin. Sennacherib and Shirin built monasteries for Mar Mattai and Abraham near Mosul.</note>
               <note type="disambiguation">goes with Sara</note>
